   "source": [
    "## Gumbel Distribution Sampler\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Gumbel distribution** (also known as the Type-I extreme value distribution) models the distribution of the *maximum* of a large number of independent, identically distributed random variables. It appears naturally in hydrology (maximum flood levels), meteorology (extreme wind speeds), and materials science (fracture strength).\n",
    "\n",
    "Its PDF is:\n",
    "$$p(x) = \\frac{1}{\\beta} e^{-(z + e^{-z})}, \\quad z = \\frac{x - \\mu}{\\beta}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\mu$ is the location (mode) and $\\beta > 0$ is the scale parameter.\n",
    "\n",
    "**numpy docs:** `numpy.random.Generator.gumbel(loc=0.0, scale=1.0, size=None)`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Draw 1000 random variates from a Gumbel distribution\n",
    "# loc=0 (mode), scale=1 (spread)\n",
    "rng = np.random.default_rng(seed=42)\n",
    "samples = rng.gumbel(loc=0.0, scale=1.0, size=1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Histogram into 100 bins and overlay the theoretical PDF\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histogram (density=True so it aligns with the PDF)\n",
    "ax.hist(samples, bins=100, density=True,\n",
    "        color='steelblue', edgecolor='white', linewidth=0.3,\n",
    "        label='Sampled data (n=1000)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Overlay the theoretical Gumbel PDF\n",
    "x = np.linspace(samples.min() - 0.5, samples.max() + 0.5, 500)\n",
    "z = x  # loc=0, scale=1\n",
    "pdf = np.exp(-(z + np.exp(-z)))\n",
    "ax.plot(x, pdf, color='tomato', linewidth=2, label='Theoretical PDF')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Value', fontsize=13)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Probability Density', fontsize=13)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Gumbel Distribution  (loc=0, scale=1)  —  1000 samples, 100 bins',\n",
    "             fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.4)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('gumbel_histogram.pdf')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Figure saved as gumbel_histogram.pdf')"
   ]
  }
 ]
}

